enhanced_by.reason: Setting new security requirements should be done before or after setting old security requirements to ensure proper comparison and state management.
Setting missing security requirements should be done after setting old security requirements to correctly identify missing requirements.
The isCoreChanged method evaluates the compatibility based on security requirements, making it a suitable candidate for assertions after setting old security requirements.
The equals method compares the state of the object, including security requirements, making it useful for asserting the correctness of the setOldSecurityRequirements method.
